Privacy Statement
Tollsmart wants to assure that Users of the Tollsmart Sites are provided with appropriate
    information and choice mechanisms about Tollsmart’s relevant policies and practices so that these Users may make informed decisions on whether or not to use the Tollsmart Sites.
This Privacy Statement is a statement of Your privacy rights, and should be read by You carefully
    before using the Tollsmart Sites. Your use of the Tollsmart Sites is Your acknowledgement of, and specific consent to, the terms and conditions of this Privacy Statement and all of the practices
    described in this Privacy Statement.
Tollsmart is committed to safeguarding Your privacy online. As Tollsmart expands its offerings and
    as technology evolves, We may, from time to time, update Our privacy practices to address such changes, and We may do so with or without notice to Users. Please check this page on a regular basis
    for updates to this Privacy Statement if these issues are of concern to You.
Please note that this Privacy Statement shall apply to You regardless of whether You access the
    Tollsmart Sites directly, whether the Tollsmart Sites are made available to You by a third party, or whether You access the Tollsmart Sites by other means. This Privacy Statement shall take
    precedence over any conflicting terms published by a third party that You may have accepted (or in the future be required to accept) in connection with Your access or use of the Tollsmart
    Sites.
THE TOLLSMART SITES, AND THE PRODUCTS, SERVICES AND ADVERTISING MADE AVAILABLE THROUGH THE TOLLSMART
    SITES, ARE NOT INTENDED FOR USE BY CHILDREN WITHOUT PARENTAL SUPERVISION.
Definitions:
“Tollsmart,” “We,” “Our,” and “Us” refers to Tollsmart, LLC and any and all entities that are
    controlled by or under common control with Tollsmart, LLC.
“Tollsmart Sites,” are comprised of and defined to include, but are not necessarily limited to, all
    Tollsmart websites, digital products, services, applications, data, content, advertising, and other elements. Such other elements may include sign up screens, data input and tracking, and other
    interfaces currently or in the future of use in the digital industry.
“Online Behavioral Advertising,” also referred to as “OBA,” which is also sometimes called
    “interest-based advertising,” uses information collected across multiple web sites that You visit in order to predict Your preferences and to show You advertisings that are most likely to be of
    interest to You.
“Privacy Statement,” refers to this statement and is specifically limited to the actual statements
    and wording contained herein and does not include things that may be inferred herefrom. If there is a lack of clarity or coverage, interpretation or use, We have the right, in Our sole
    discretion, to interpret the nature of the rights hereunder.
“Personally Identifiable Information,” (often referred to herein by the letters “PII”) means any
    information by which a person could be specifically identified, including but not limited to name, address, email address, and information about the approximate or precise location of a person
    and/or his or her device. PII also includes any related information, whether supplied specifically by the User, supplied by the User’s device, or inferable from the use of the device or other
    applications, that might lead to knowledge about the User. Your username and any password supplied by You is also PII. In addition to the PII obtained at registration and during use, You may be
    asked for information at other times, such as when You make a purchase or register for a service on or through the Tollsmart Sites, when You submit information or when You report a problem with
    the Tollsmart Sites. Your PII also may be provided indirectly to Tollsmart during your use of a device by the manufacturer of the device or your internet service provider subject to their own
    terms of service. Please also be aware that whenever You voluntarily disclose PII online - for example on message boards, through email, or in chat areas –that information can be collected and
    used by others.
“Providers,” refers to non-Tollsmart entities such as, but not limited to, service providers,
    advertisers, vendors, data collection services and other third parties. These Providers may also collect information about You.
“Special Programs,” refers to certain promotions, surveys, sweepstakes, contests or similar
    activities on the Tollsmart Sites.
“User,” “You,” “Your,” and “Visitor,” whether in the singular or plural refers to anyone who views,
    downloads or interacts with any of the Tollsmart Sites.
What We
    Collect About You.
We collect information, including PII, on the Tollsmart Sites
    during the registration process and through Your use of the Tollsmart Sites that We believe will allow us to better and more efficiently serve You. Our personalization, interactive
    communications, online commerce, targeted or contextual advertising, data access or accumulation, location tracking and services, receipt of device transmitted information, and other types of
    activities and services, allow us to deliver better service and content We believe is relevant to Our user base and You.
Some uses Tollsmart makes of this information are processing and verifying subscriptions, billing,
    delivering targeted or contextual advertising, and providing You with up-to-date information on Tollsmart products, services, advertising and those things described in the definition of the
    Tollsmart Sites above. The information we collect may be utilized by Tollsmart to, among other things, host, or use in conjunction with, the operation of the Tollsmart Sites and the products,
    services, and advertising related to them.
You may be asked to provide information that personally identifies You or allows Tollsmart and/or
    its Providers to identify or contact You. Such information may be requested when You are asked to register for fee-based services, although some free products and services may also request or
    require registration. For example, We may request personal information from You when You create an account, download an application or content through the Tollsmart Sites, enter information on
    the Tollsmart Sites, subscribe to e-mail newsletters or other content made available by the Tollsmart Sites, or report a problem with Your account or the Tollsmart Sites. As a registered
    subscriber or user, You may be able to download software, enter contests or sweepstakes, order e-mail newsletters or participate in additional services or other promotions offered on the
    Tollsmart Sites.
In addition to the information that You may proactively provide or voluntarily disclose, Your use of
    the Tollsmart Sites may result in the assignment of unique identifying numbers and/or codes which may be used to allow Tollsmart and its Providers and others who assist Tollsmart in the support
    of the Tollsmart Sites to track Your web browsing movements across the internet. By using the Tollsmart Sites, You acknowledge and consent to such activity.
To provide location-based and contextual advertisements, location related products and services, and
    other things that may benefit from knowing or inferring Your location, Tollsmart and Providers utilize certain geographic tracking technologies that may collect, use, and/or share precise
    location data (such as GPS signals sent by a mobile device) or information that may be used to approximate a location (such as, but not limited to, a cell ID or IP address), including the
    real-time geographic location of Your computer or mobile device. By using the Tollsmart Sites, You consent to use by Tollsmart and its Providers of such geographic tracking technologies.
You should be aware that the fact that You turn off location services may not mean that all location
    identifiable technologies are turned off. Your device may only turn off GPS tracking, but many devices in the marketplace also track and transmit other location information such as use of
    Bluetooth (if enabled), identification of a Wi-Fi router through which a device may be communicating, and personal IP address. Some devices even transmit information such as battery power and
    charging status. We may have no control over how Your device is functioning or transmitting information to Us or others in these modes, which transmission is subject to the terms of service of
    your phone manufacturer or internet service provider.
If You contact Tollsmart We may keep a record of that contact or correspondence, and may prompt You
    for further information, depending on the nature of the contact. We may also occasionally ask that You voluntarily participate in or enable automatic entry into Special Programs via log-on
    entries. At such times, Tollsmart may disclose Your PII to sponsors of the Special Program, and We may or may not describe this to You prior to transferring the data. Special Programs may also be
    subject to additional or different terms, or may be shared or used in a slightly different way. If different terms do apply, details of the specific terms and conditions or rules for these
    Special Programs may or may not be provided by posting to the Tollsmart Sites or upon registration for the Special Program, on a case-by-case basis, subject to Tollsmart's terms for sharing
    PII.
Why We
    Want to Know Certain Information.
It's important for Us to know Our users. We
    deliver valuable information to You on the Tollsmart Sites free of charge or at low rates. We are able to accomplish this through the use of Providers to produce the income to operate the
    Tollsmart Sites. Providers are like most businesses in that they want something in return for the money they spend advertising on the Tollsmart Sites or otherwise providing value. They may want
    to know how many people will see their advertisements, for example, and how often these advertisements are seen. The advertising companies may use information (including or not including PII)
    about Your visits to this and other web sites in order to provide advertisements about goods and services believed to be of interest to You. These companies may also employ, among other things,
    Cookies, Web Beacons, Flash Shared Objects, HTML5 Local Storage and/or HTML5 Mini Databases in furtherance of their services to Tollsmart.
Among other things, Tollsmart and its Providers use the information You provide, or Your device
    provides, including PII to: fulfill Your request for products, services, or information; to process and administer Your entry in Special Programs; to activate Your account; to allow You to access
    fee-based parts of the Tollsmart Sites; and, to allow You to submit information (e.g., routes, vehicle specifications) to Tollsmart or its Providers. We may also use such information (including
    PII) to notify You of changes to the Tollsmart Sites; to provide You with e-mail offers, text message offers, and other promotional opportunities; to provide You with up-to-date information on
    the newest Tollsmart products and services that may be of interest to You; to handle billing issues with You; and to tailor Our online offerings to Your preferences.
